var cardDescriptions = {41084: "The Light Emperor, first king of the Light Nation. In his\ryouth, he led his army in battle against 400,000 soldiers from\rthe north. After claiming victory, he was elected king by 36\rwarlords, and established the capital city of Everfall.",
41085: "The Frost Emperor, a great king who unified the north and\rexpanded his rule southward. Aftering suffering defeat at the\rhands of Alexander, he retreated back to the north frontier\rand built Glacier City, capital of the Frost Nation.",
41772: "The headstrong Emperor of the Flame Nation, and patriarch\rof the Fire Dragon Clan. With unshakable pride and ambition,\rhe established Durna, capital of the Flame Nation.",
41773: "The daughter of Janice, the first Dark Empress. She inherited\rthe throne at the tender age of 18 and built the City of Peace,\rwhere she ruled as the Dark Empress.",
41774: "The Dark Emperor, a man of the sea and master naval strategist,\rleads the Twilight Empire and rules the waters. Though he is an\remperor, his appearance and mannerisms are like those of a sea\rbrigand.",
41775: "The emperor of the Primal World. After the gods abandoned the\rPrimal World, he ensured the survival of his people and built a\rnew empire.He eventually became a greedy Tyrant hated by all.",
41784: "The noble queen of the Light Nation. A strong but benevolent\rruler, she is greatly adored by all her people and soldiers.",
41785: "The empress of the Frost Nation, she eternally craves absolute\rpower. When she blows her horn, hundreds of thousands of\rbarbarians will respond with a roar.",
41786: "Astrid is short, but fiery-tempered.\rAs the Dragonborne, she can withstand fire and tame dragons.",
41787: "Though gentle in appearance, Lorelei, queen of the Twilight\rEmpire, is a true veteran of the seas. She is the captain of\rthe Dragonlord, an impressive warship. Sharp and aloof, she can\rcome across as intimidating even to her own soldiers.",
41788: "The pike is the most difficult blade to wield with control. And\ryet, despite his young age, Gu Hensin wields it as if it were a\rpart of his body.",
41789: "Lio Gianni is one of the Four Great Commanders. In the Battle\rof Two Cities, the Winged Elves dispatched all of their elite\rtroops, but Lio Gianni's brilliant strategies pushed them back\rwhile optimizing the city's defenses.",
41790: "Tsen the Heavensent, one of the Four Great Commanders, does not\rhave any family. Contrary to his nickname, he is a cruel man on\rthe battlefield, showing no mercy to his enemies.",
41791: "The charismatic leader of Four Great Commanders. He has\r claimed countless victories in battle, even when outnumbered. \rThis valiant man was feared by the Winged Elves. Unfortunately,\rthe gods took him away, for his godlike strength threw the world\rinto imbalance.",
41792: "Feng Lorie, the Tideborn's ancestor, was a brave and resourceful\rman. He killed Turoho, the evil god of the Nightspikes, with Lunar\rDissector, putting an end to the war between the Tideborn and the\rNightspikes, which had lasted for a thousand years.",
41793: "It is extremely difficult to reverse the Dimensional Cataclysm.\rAs the priestess of this ritual, Feng Drime overdrew her entire\rsoulforce to stop the curse from getting out of control, sacri-\rficing her life and soul for the sake of the Tideborn.",
41794: "The king of the Tideborn who fought valiantly on the battle-\rfield for the survival of his people. Now, Feng Triton sits in\rhis palace above Raging Tide, picking up the wand or blowing\rthe horn now and then. Perhaps he is reminiscing on his days\rat war.",
41795: "The incumbent general who defends Plume City. Jen is an outsta-\rnding Winged Elf archer. It is said that anyone hit by Jen's\rice arrow will turn into a wisp of smoke.",
41796: "The incumbent general who defends Etherblade City. Chung's\rfather and grandfather also held this post before him. Chung\rdeeply loved Loyan, the daughter of the City Lord. After Loyan\rdied, the heartbroken Chung chose to remain single.",
41797: "The incumbent general who defends the City of the Lost. \rGeneral Po is a master of forging weapons and armor. He once\rforged a set of extraordinary armor with the materials that he\rfound in the Twilight Temple. This armor made him nearly\rinvincible.",
41798: "When the City of a Thousand Streams was built, all races and\rfactions sent their elites to stay in the Worldspire, making the\rcity a decisive force and global mediator in Perfect World. The\rElder of the Streams is the spokesman of the city and makes all\rthe important decisions that could affect all of Perfect World.",
41799: "As the most famous of the five major capitals, Archosaur is the\rcenter of political and cultural exchanges in Perfect World. All\rElders of Archosaur have, in the past, wholly devoted themselves\rto serving this city.",
41800: "Selected by the gods, Radiance was the founder of Earthguard.\rTo defeat Dark Radiance, his evil counterpart, Radiance sacri-\rficed his own body. Since then, Radiance's nuema went missing.\rIt is said that the Illusive Faerie of the Forsaken Temple once\rcaught a glimpse of Radiance's wandering nuema.",
41801: "Radiance's dark half, formed from his evil thoughts. Seeking\rabsolute power, Dark Radiance devoured wraiths to strengthen\rhimself. After Radiance destroyed himself, Dark Radiance was\rsaved by the Wraith Lord, in turn becoming his executioner and\rslaughtering his victims.",
41802: "The king of the Mighty Wings, one of four ancient Winged Elf\rnations. Allying with the other Winged Elf nations, he once\rcrusaded against the Twilight Empire. Protected by the Might of\rthe Great Goose, he survived the Twilight Disaster.",
41803: "An ancient Winged Elf king. Allying with Ien the Arbor, he\rhelped defeat the Twilight Empire's army.",
41804: "An ancient Winged Elf king. Allying with the Feather Lord, he\rhelped defeat the Twilight Empire's army.",
41805: "An ancient Winged Elf king famous for defeating General Chongo\rin the battle against the Twilight Empire.",
41806: "The second minister of the Twilight Empire, as well as the\rleader of a faction supporting Prince Chongming. She orchest-\rrated the undercover uprising within the Twilight Empire along\rwith Tsuan. She also started the Wheel of Fate in the battle\ragainst the Winged Elf Alliance that resulted in the destruction\rof the Twilight Empire.",
41807: "An outstanding Winged Elf warrior. To overthrow the Twilight\rEmpire, Tsuan removed her plumes through the Sacrilege Ceremony\rand became the minister of Twilight Empire along with Tsu. They\rcleverly orchestrated an internal takeover of the Twilight\rEmpire's forces.",
41808: "A brave warrior with a penchant for flamboyant poetry.",
41809: "Frost Ancient's brother, who was deserted at a burial site for\rdead infants. He survived by eating corpses and bones, and made\ra contract with Fientazzar, the enemy of Frostcovered City's\rguardian. He swore to rebuild Frostcovered City for himself and\rrespect Fientazzar as his god. He is known for his sadistic\rfighting style.",
41810: "Vanished Ancestor, the grand wraith wizard, is sealed away in\rthe Temple of the Forbidden Coast by the Tideborn.",
41811: "The Harpy Wraith is a master of the dreaded Soul Trap. It has\rthe power to control the souls around it, and once the soul is\rcontrolled, it is forever slave to the Harpy Wraith.",
41812: "Lord Isrifar's awakened form. It is said that his obsession with\rpower drove him to become a demon.",
41813: "The commander of Archosaur, and a descendant of Lio Gianni. He\rleads the Allied Force against the Wraith Army, and is known as\rthe 'Iron Fortress of Archosaur.'",
41814: "Tsang, once a lord of Everfall, has become a hideous undead\rwalker of the illusory world",
41815: "Dorian's daughter, known as the Beauty of the East. Since the\rcivil war, she has been imprisoned in the Desert Tower. No one\rhas known of her whereabouts since General Chungyun went to\rrescue her.",
41816: "General Chungyun was a pioneer of the Twilight Army, succeeding\rin defending the Twilight Empire from the Winged Elves' siege.\rAfter the Plain War, he was appointed to bring the Princess of\rMoonlight back from the Desert Tower. However, he disappeared\rtogether with the Princess of Moonlight after defeating the\rNimbustians.",
41817: "Legendary devils who exist solely to destroy. When the Twilight\rEmpire was going through a great crisis, Minister Tsu activated\rthe Wheel of Fate to release the sealed ancient devils. The\rceremonylasted for 49 days, consuming rich sacrificial offer-\rings. However, an accidenthappened, and the devils destoryed\rthe Twilight Empire.",
41818: "The creator of the Illusory World. After breaking away from the\rgods, she created an illusory world in which dead, powerful\rcreatures are revived. She summons ancient mystical powers to\rstrengthen the illusory world, hoping to replace the world created\rby the gods with her undead world.",
41819: "The highest priest of Winged Elf who believes that the gods will\rreturn someday. Managing the internal affairs in Plume City along-\rside the Elders, she is considered the spiritual leader of the\rWinged Elves.",
41820: "An Elder of five races, in charge of Winged Elf affairs.",
41821: "An Elder of five races, in charge of Human affairs.",
41822: "An Elder of five races, in charge of Earthguard affairs.",
41823: "An Elder of Earthguard, enjoying the highest prestige in the \rSacred Word. He can hear the whispers from gods, converting\rthose poor souls into Earthguards..",
41824: "The wraiths in the Deserted Sea near the Hidden Dragon Den\rspent many years creating a powerful devil. Hiding deep in the\rHidden Dragon Den, the ferocious devil waits for people who are\rled there by the Fire Dragon Clan.",
41825: "An Elder of five races, in charge of Untamed affairs.",
41826: "Wild and strong from birth, he was give nthe title 'King of Beasts'\rby the Untamed Elders for his great war feats. In his later years,\rhe pioneered many skills that are now essential, such as Stomp of\rthe Beast King, Beast King's Inspiration, Bestial Onslaught, and\rBestial Rage.",
41827: "Absorbing the consciousness of all beings in this world, the\rWheel of Eternity grew a self-awareness that attracts wraiths.\rAurogon, the serpent demon, was born as a result of this.",
41828: "This brilliant inventor designed the Human's crystal-powered\rAerosword, and helped the Untamed domesticate the first Sparrow\rHawks.",
41829: "In the middle of the first Millennium War, a gravely ill man\rfrom the Primal World helped the Humans with his marvelous\rpyrocraft. He made some improvements to the pyrogram spell,\rgreatly enhancing its firing range. These developments turned\rthe tide of battle.",
41830: "The first queen of the Ancestral Land, and the mother of Mayen,\rthe Green Empress. She fell in Pon Jay, a wizard from Etherblade\rCity who later died in a battle against the Fire Dragon Clan.\rWhen Mayen was old enough to inherit the throne, Janice\rpeacefully joined her husband in death.",
41831: "Grand Wizard Tensa is the most powerful Human wizardof all time.\rShe is the one who created the Undine Strike and Soporific Whisper\rtechniques.",
41832: "As a disciple of Tensa, Soul Controller Saki became the first\rpsychic. Due to her ability to control soulforce instead of\relements, Saki was not regarded by traditional wizards. Instead,\rshe taught her skills to the Tideborn, who were eager to achieve\rpsychic powers.",
41833: "The supreme commander of the Wraith Army, and a man of great\rwisdom and power, he takes charge of this mysterious army under\rthe orders of the Wraith Ancestor. Fearless and uncompromising,\rhe marches forward in battle with frightening willpower.",
41834: "A powerful man who controls the Archosaur Commanders. He is as\rambitious as he is calculating, always watching and waiting in\rsilence for the perfect strike.",
41835: "An outstanding general who is greatly respected by his subordinates.",
41836: "An elusive ancient beast from Lothranis.",
41837: "An elusive ancient beast from Momaganon.",
41838: "One of Three Demons from Abaddon who has slaughtered countless\rinnocent people.",
41839: "One of Three Demons in Abaddon who possesses boundless strength.",
41840: "One of Three Demons in Abaddon who tortures\rits victims with fire magic.",
41841: "Infernal Spikewing, one of the Three Fallen Celestials, was\ronce a defender of Lothranis. Tempted by the evil power in the\rSeat of Torment, his body deformed into that of a hideous demon.",
41842: "Rancid Venerator, one of the Three Fallen Celestials, was once\ra defender of Lothranis. Tempted by the evil power in the Seat\rof Torment, his body deformed into that of a hideous demon.",
41843: "Torturess Venerator, one of the Three Fallen Celestials, was once\ra defender of Lothranis. Tempted by the evil power in the Seat\rof Torment, her body deformed into that of a hideous beast.",
41844: "Since the City of Abominations was built, the creatures living\rthere have been protecting a secret magic buried underground.\rRumor has it that it was a forbidden magic of destructive power.\rWhen the nine stars formed a straight line Dread Lord Hengchih\rtook the opportunity to occupy the City of Abominations, in\rorder to get the secret magic.",
41845: "Born in discord and buried in silence, Chaos is the omnipotent\roverlord of everything. He has the power to influence fate itself.",
41846: "A war hero of the Primal World, Wolfen Ironside is powerful\rand mighty. However, he is cruel and boorish to people.",
41847: "A demon formed completely from essences, unbound by the laws\rof physics. She is as old as the universe itself. It is impossible\r to kill such a demon.",
41848: "Ultimate Stance is an intelligent beast proficient in\rwarcraft. All beasts revere him.",
41849: "In ancient books, this god is often described as a being that\rgoverns the elemental powers and is one with the universe.",
41850: "He used to be an immortal poet. Because of his immortality, he\rlacked appreciation for life and death, and was corrupted by\revil. He coins beautiful lyrics as he murders his victims.",
41851: "A beautiful butterfly spirit inhabiting the valleys. Its long\rcultivationhas blessed it with great power - power that it will\rnot hesitate to use against strangers.",
41852: "One of the Raksa Lords, who presides over the Demonic Prison.\rHer biggest obsession is inventing new torture devices and list-\rening to the prisoners' screams.",
41853: "The Dismal Duke is one of the few intellectual Wraiths, and is\ra cruel extremist. His radical nature and insane boldness have\rwon him a high reputation among the Wraiths. His Wraith divisions\rfamous for their speed, often showing appearing out of nowhere\rin unexpected places. Once they almost marched into Archosaur\rCity. Many Wraiths believe he is the greatest among their ranks,\rand their true leader.",
41854: "A suit of armor worn by its dead owner in an ancient tomb. The\rdark, arcane power of the tomb gave the armor sentience. Rest-\rless, it began to protect its master's corpsepunishing all who\rdare venture into the tomb.",
41855: "A champion of the Hidden Dragon Den monsters who craves the\rpower of fire, believing it is the only true strength. This\robsessive belief, however, led it to the dark side.",
41856: "Once a close friend to Fei Kungxing and Yeh Kuhan, he abandoned\rhis friends due to their differences and pursued the demonic\rway. However, he still possesses a pitiful heart.",
41857: "Once a close friend to Chin Wuming and Yeh Kuhan, he abandoned\rhis friends due to their differences. He was nearly killed by the\rThundersoul Beast when during his weakest moment. The beast\rcontinues to haunt him in his nightmares.",
41858: "'Only the fallen leaf knows that it is autumn.\rEvery night it sleeps in frosty tears.'",
41859: "An immortal king who led the ancient people of Perfect World\rand Morai in the war that defeated Aurogon and brought many\ryears of peace.",
41860: "The mysterious leader of the Shroud. His unique magical powers\rallow him to walk freely among the living and the dead.",
41861: "The man who leads a large army made of elites from Corona and\rShroud. He built the army in support of the\balance of powers,\rmaking him one of three great powers. However, no one knows his\rtrue identity.",
41862: "A low-ranking envoy of the Divine Furies, whose duty is\rto present newbies with quests.",
41863: "A middle-rank envoy of Divine Furies, whose duty is distributing\rquests for meditators with some experience.",
41864: "A high-ranking envoy of the Divine Furies, whose duty is\rto present veteran warriors with quests.",
41865: "An envoy sent to Corona by the Divine Furies. It seems that\revery major warof the past was related to the Divine Furies.",
41866: "An envoy sent to Shroud by the Divine Furies. It seems that every\rmajor warof the past was related to the Divine Furies.",
41867: "An envoy sent to Luminance by the Divine Furies. It seems that every major war\rof the past was related to the Divine Furies.",
41868: "The Puppeteer is the most loyal servant of the Borobudur Dungeon Lord. He\rguards the gate to his lord's chamber and shows no mercy to\rthose who set foot into the place. He often imprisons his victims\rin a tiny room until they break down in madness.",
41869: "The Mask of Grief was born from the good side of Lord Borobudur.\rHowever, it is still bound to the evil lord, forced to do its\rbidding. It bravely asked to be killed by a warrior of justice,\rso as to weaken its evil half.",
41870: "Peachblossom Ritualist's sister, who also lived in Lothranis.\rAfter Peachblossom Fairy bacame Peachblossom Ritualist, she\rfollowed her to Momaganon and abandoned her celestial form.",
41871: "Lord Borobudur possesses god-like power. He was contained by a\rgroup of seven celestial warriors after a five day fight and\rsealed in Abaddon. When Peachblossom Ritualist was injured,\rhe broke the seal and began his conquest of Momaganon.",
41872: "'Do you truly wish to give up life as a celestial being and\rbecome a demon?' asked the Celestial Demon. The Fairy answered,\r'I am no longer the person I was. There's no place in the Celestial\rRealm for me anymore. Please take me away.'",
41873: "The Queen of Demons. As a powerful, respected, and ambitious\rwarrior, she may be intending to usurp the Hellfire Abomination's\rrule.",
41874: "The demon lord who followed Queen Xipher after the Seat of\rTorment changed. He is an expert machinist who guards the Hell\rTrap for Queen Xipher, while preparing new forces for the reborn\rdarkness.",
41875: "The bastard son of the Hellfire Abomination. He inherited his\rfather's short temper. After the Hellfire Abomination was locked\rinside the Seat of Torment, he became more aggessive and was\rfinally imprisoned in Seat of Torment as well.",
41876: "He once lived in Lothranis but was exiled to the Seat of\rTorment due to his cruel ways. The agony in the Seat of\rTorment intensifies his hatred for the world.",
41877: "Guard Seven, defender of the west gate of Archosaur, bears no\rsympathy for the evil. He kills all wraiths and outlaws who come\rnear the gate.",
41878: "The cunning East Sovereign of Morai. He is a trickster who can\rtransform into different people. Shrewd and silent, he hides his\rown ambition when giving advice to Aurogon. He organizes a faction\rwith Yakku and Biran, conspiring on the sly.",
41879: "The miserly North Sovereign of Morai. Biran is despised by\rAurogon because he is a greedy coward. Aohe drew Biran to his\rside, valuing his powerful strength. Biran will betray anyone\ras long as it's profitable to do so.",
41880: "The headstrong Central Sovereign of Morai. Deeply trusted by\rAurogon, Chigo draws up the final plan. He kills Glory, the Elder's\rson, and takes on his appearance. Then, he activates the Undying\rDial, attempting to rebuild the wraith land.",
41881: "The beautiful but capricious West Sovereign of Morai. Sometimes,\rshe is sweet and mild. Sometimes, she is quite cold-blooded. She\rhates men very much, but she obeys Aohe's every word.",
41882: "The proud Upper Sovereign of Morai. As the overlord in the sky,\rhe possesses the sharpest eyes amongst the Sovereigns. Looking\rdown upon the other five sovereigns, he is only loyal and devoted\rto Aurogon, and ruthless to all creatures who enter his airspace.",
41883: "The bloodthirsty South Sovereign of Morai. To him, there is no\rbetter pleasure than killing and pillaging. Leaving fire and\rdestruction in his wake, Locen truly is a monster.",
41884: "Duke Blacke is a knowledgeable man who lives in Archosaur. It\ris said that he has seven beautiful wives.",
41885: "There is a gorgeous fairy living in the Frozen Hall of Frost-\rcovered City. You can only win her favor with Sincerity.",
41886: "She was once the princess of Tideborn. Tricked by \rVanished Ancestor, she fell into Palace of Nirvana \rand became Ashura Netherqueen.",
41887: "A mystical woman with breathtaking beauty. It is saidrthat she\has the most alluring voice and dancing postures. But,no one\rknows where she came from or how she ended up in Perfect World.\rNumerous people around the world seek her, hoping to lay their\reyes upon her beauty.",
41888: "A mystical and unfathomable warrior of the Wraith Army. It is\rsaid that he was transformed by the resentful souls of dead\rwraiths. This intense hatred grants him mysterious power. He\rhas sworn to kill everyone who challenges the Wraith Army.",
41889: "The powerful grand wizard of the Wraith Army. Residing in the\rdark demonic lake, he is odd and morose. Almost everyone who\rattempts to approach him is killed by his immense power.",
41890: "The lonely and bloodthirsty swordsman of the Wraith Army. He\rwanders the underworld all day long, killing every living thing\rin his path.",
41891: "A ruthless fighter of the Wraith Army. Nobody\rknows where he came from. With his flaming\rhammer, this strapping man kills everyone\rwho challenges the Wraith Army.",
41892: "An evil sorcerer of the Wraith Army. His noble blood endows him\rwith fearsome magic powers, which have earned him the respect of\rthe Wraiths.",
41893: "Humans are sociable, and the majority of them choose lives as\rmerchants and diplomats. Yet the few who take up arms are by no\rmeans less able. Gifted with an amazing flexibility, Humans\radapt easily to every new situation.",
41894: "Wizards prefer to cast damaging spells from a distance. Though\rthey are masters of damaging Water, Fire, and Earth, their bodies\rare weak and not good at close combat.",
41895: "The Untamed are descendants of the animals \rthat evolved sentience. With berserker rage \rand animal cunning, they still carry the \rbeast in their hearts.",
41896: "True to their heritage as self-aware foxes, serpents, and other\rvermin, the Venomancers are subtle, relying on poisons or curses\rto bring down enemies. They can also control animals or transform\rinto foxes for an additional set of skills.",
41897: "Archers hail from an ancient and divine bloodline. \rTheir exquisite form and unique wings grant them \rthe ability to fly. As the guardian of Winged Elf, they \rare outstanding archers and brave warriors, good at \rusing ranged weapons like the bow.",
41898: "The Winged Elves are the most beautiful people among their\rcontemporaries. Gifted with flight from a young age, they can\rbe seemingly aloof and reclusive. Yet, those who are familiar\rwith them, find Winged Elves to be staunch allies.",
41899: "Striking from the shadows, a dagger in the back, and a silent\rretreat are trademarks of an Assassin. Assassins are not brute\rmelee fighters, but masters of finesse. They prefer to rely on\ragility rather than bulky armor.",
41900: "The Tideborn class no longer pursue mastery of the elements,\rbut now manipulate the essence and instincts of creatures.\rThey manifest their will through Soulforce to enhance them-\rselves and their allies while harming their enemies.",
41901: "Seekers train in both the martial and arcane arts, and use the\relement of metal to enhance their close-combat swordplay. Each\rSeeker bears a relic upon their forehead that can discern evil.",
41902: "A Mystic affects others with their grace and tenderness. With\rthe ability to communicate with the spiritual beings of nature,\rthey summon them as weapons. Vines, thorns, and trees are just a\rfraction of their arsenal. A Mystic also possesses miraculous\rhealing power, providing full support to teammates during combat.",
41903: "A valiant warlord whose origins are a mystery. He sometimes\rcomes to Perfect World to recruit the strongest of warriors\rinto the war between the four nations. He does not seem to\rhave a dedicated alliance with any of the nations.",
41904: "A lovely fairy who helps deal with pet affairs \rin Archosaur.",
41905: "Lord Isrifar presides over the Guardian Trials. He has\ra mad obsession with power.",
41906: "The powerful patriarch of the Blackhive wolves, Rend\rRazorjaw is an enormously powerful beast that is\reasily a match for even the mightiest of barbarians.",
41907: "The cave along the River of Tranquility was once a peaceful\rplace, until the Wraiths came. Once the queen of the poisontail\rscorpions, the Poisontail Occultist was heavily corrupted by the\rWraiths, transforming her into a twisted monstrosity.",
41908: "Thromh the Mighty is a Wraith of unparalleled strength.\rWhen the seal on the gateway within Firecrag Grotto weakened,\rhe emerged into Perfect World to sow chaos and destruction.",
41909: "Farng was onced a talented stylite, but later degenerated \rand fell into the abyss of sin.",
41910: "With a massive sound, a monster appeared at the Hill of the \rOld King. It's called Eyes of the Krimson Beyond.",
41911: "On the Broken Plain north of Sumor Camp, wolves come \rand go in packs. Suzerix, Adalwolf Elder, is the leader.",
41912: "Commander Fugma, Archmage Kashu and the Omnipotent Drake \rare deeply feared around the Fortress of the Talon.",
41913: "Commander Fugma, Archmage Kashu and the Omnipotent Drake \rare deeply feared around the Fortress of the Talon.",
41914: "Commander Fugma, Archmage Kashu and the Omnipotent Drake \rare deeply feared around the Fortress of the Talon.",
41915: "You hear a sharp scream from the sky. \rIt's Jewelscalen, who claimed Skull Mountain.",
41916: "The Tauroc Clan and its leader, Viriddis Stormhorn \rclaimed that they were the only witnesses to \rwhat befell the Town of Arrivals.",
41917: "Qingzi was once the senior apprentice to the great meditator Farng.\rWhen the Wraiths attacked, Qingzi was overwhelmed by the Wraiths and killed.\rThe Wraiths stole his body and reanimated him as a terrible monster.",
41918: "The Wraiths appointed their two strongest guards to\rpatrol the Wraithgate. The Damned Gaurnob's power\rand ferocity are nearly unmatched.",
41919: "The Wraiths appointed two of their strongest guards\rto patrol the Wraithgate. Though Cenequus Polearm\rcommands the entire Dreadmarsh Legion, he is not\runwilling to impale intruders upon his spear.",
41920: "Do you still remember their defeat a decade ago?\rThe last words of Chin, Mausoleum Watchman were oaths\rof vengeance.",
41921: "The Nightspike Bloodguard advanced quickly with the\rHoly Mirror of Heaven. He hid in the depths of the ocean\r after failing to attack the City of Misfortune.",
41922: "'Dirty intruders, now pay for your curiosity!'\rThe wandering ghosts protect the Twilight Temple forever.",
41923: "Follower of ancient devils, a byproduct of Tsu's\rsummoning ceremony. Strong and terrifying.",
41924: "The Raging Lion, previously under the banner of Chungyun,\rwas overrun by the Winged Elves in The Plain War. \rHis current whereabouts are a mystery.",
41925: "Tamed by Tsu for obedience. Massive in size and strength.",
41926: "Warden, previously a guard of the Desert Tower, \rsurvived Chungyun in his raid for the Princess \rof Moonlight.",
41927: "A high-ranking official of the Twilight Empire, originally \rhandsome and tall. Under the influence of the ancient devils, \rhe became a ghostlike creature and screamed \rday and night.",
41928: "Spirit of the ancient devil. Ruthless and brutal.",
41929: "Tamed by Tsu and easily angered. Exceedingly rare.",
41930: "A mobster captain, later summoned by Tsu to become \rcaptain of the cloister guards.",
41931: "Extracted from Deathflow in flame. Swore allegiance to Deathflow.",
41932: "Grave Robber. Died while digging for Twilight Empire relics.",
41933: "Cloister guards of Bloodthirst, neutral in the civil war. \rSent to guard the Princess of Moonlight and destroyed \rby Chungyun.",
41934: "Cloister Guard Captain, merged with his mount and armor \runder the influence of ancient devils. \rUndead and senseless.",
41935: "An executioner. Killing is all he desires.",
41936: "Fights under the banner of Chungyun. Rude and brutal. \rFollowed the ancient devils.",
41937: "A lover of science and magic. Made himself into an \rundead monster.",
41938: "Suspected to be a descendent of ancient gods and the \rmastermind behind the doom of the Twilight Empire \rand the theft of the Golden Mask.",
41939: "Founding warrior of the Twilight Empire. \rRumored to be dead. Resurrected for a conspiracy.",
41940: "Originally king of Windblast Kingdom. Betrayed the \rTwilight Empire in the rebellion of Winged Elves, resulting \rin the destruction of the Twilight Legion.",
41941: "A wandering ghost outside the City of the Plume. \rDied after betraying her husband.",
41942: "Child prodigy, recruited by Corona. Made unique \rcontributions to the order.",
41943: "The third best warrior of Shroud, in charge of armament \rdevelopment and military supplies.",
41944: "The brain of Luminance, respected for his battle \rstrategy and logistics.",
41945: "First advisor of Corona, known for his talent-finding ability.",
41946: "Second best warrior and Chief Interrogation Officer of Shroud.",
41947: "Chief General of Luminance. Tired of battle.",
41948: "A kind of monstrous practitioner with an attractive \rappearance, interested only in the good hearts of humans.",
41949: "Naturally bred devil, formed from resentment and debris.",
41950: "Ghostly bred devil with powerful eyes, guardian \rof The Lunar Glade.",
41951: "Ghostly bred devil, formed from void wraiths.",
41952: "Naturally bred devil, formed from resentment of contact with dragonkin.",
41953: "Naturally bred devil, formed from creatures who died in floods.",
41954: "Practitioner of dark magic, equipped with powerful hands.",
41955: "Organically bred devil, descendent of tigers.",
41956: "Organically bred devil, known to feast on the internal organs of humans.",
41957: "Ghostly bred devil with the belief that killing accomplished \rpractitioners will bring it enlightenment.",
41958: "Ghostly bred devil, a practitioner of spiritual cultivation \runtil he fell into darkness because of his extreme nature.",
41959: "Known for his dark armor and dual hammers. It's said that \rhis power comes from the gems embedded in \rhis hammers.",
41960: "Whose blood saturated the moon? After the death of \rthis lonely and evil woman, her name and last words \rbecame legend.",
41961: "A headless monster, its iron shell is filled with\rmysterious power which recalls to people\rtheir sad memories.",
41962: "The companion of Lunaweaver, she seems like the other face of the moon.",
41963: "'The sword is in my hand, and I will slay the gods!'\rA male human with a good appearance.\rHe acts on emotion rather than thinking things through.",
41964: "'The shadow of the blood is splashing.'\rA female human with a good appearance.\rShe acts on emotion rather than thinking things through.\rShe was born to subdue the gods' power,\rand now she seeks to prevent their revival.",
41965: "A bearlike creature.\rIt has the ability to seal gods!",
41966: "One half of Wang Tali, he controls Insularum Valley\rwith the purpose of establishing a peaceful, loving and harmonious country.\rHe orders that different sexes should live in different areas,\rand forces everyone each day to write \ra poem praising their community.",
41967: "The younger brother of Wang Kuai.\rHe fell madly in love with a toy that belongs to Wang Erhli.\rHe's always dreamed of living together with Wang Erhli.",
41968: "The wife of Zoologist Yin.\rShe helps Venomancers manage their land pets.",
41969: "The husband of the Eldest Matchmaker.\rHe helps Venomancers mange their water pets.",
41970: "A legendary venomancer, the ex-owner of the Khatru Pup.\rShe was victimized by a scheme and was accused of betraying her people.\rFortunately she realized her fault at last, \rand now she is imprisoned to remedy her guilt.",
41971: "A lonely ghost outside Orchid Temple.\rWith the help of Redglow the Taoist \rand Fang the Scholar she was finally reincarnated.",
41972: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts,\rit killed all the people in the Fortress of the \rTalon in order to get the Talon Chart.",
41973: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts, \rit led the Adalwolf army to invade the Alliance's camps.",
41974: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts,\rit has two horns and a bat wing,\rand takes Skull Mountain as its base.",
41975: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts, \rit led a horde of Wraiths to attack Heaven's Tear.",
41976: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts,\rit tried to open the gateway linking our world together \rwith the other world in order to summon otherworldly \rhorrors to aid them in the war against us.",
41977: "One of The Seven Wraithbeasts,\rit led the Wraith legions to invade Tusk Town.",
41978: "Lv1 mob in the starting village.",
41979: "Lv1 mob in the starting village.",
41980: "Lv1 mob in the starting village.",
41981: "The Treasure Cave of Nightscream Isle was once one of the \rmost wealthy and luxurious caves around in the world. \rEach night, pirates would haul their booty to this place.\rAmong them, the Chief Assassin is the cruelest.",
41982: "The five races exile their criminals to Tusk Town,\rwhich has become a haven for thieves and brigands.",
41983: "After the Wraiths invaded, Perfect World was \rno longer safe, including Sanctuary.",
41984: "Seaspray Bladewolf desired to occupy Dreamweaver Port.\rThanks to General Tuyan's intelligent commands, the port was not destroyed.",
41985: "Araneid Cruelhearts range outside the Camp of the Intrepid.\rThey are fierce and poisonous.",
41986: "Chipmunq Gluttons like eating tough stones,\respecially those soaked by Araneid Cruelhearts' venom.",
41987: "North of the Camp of the Intrepid live a great number of Decaying Cleavehands.\rThey are tall, ugly and powerful.",
41988: "The Harshlands are located in the northwestern corner of Perfect World.\rThey is a snow-capped and deserted place, and home to the Nivastok Shieldbearers.\rFerocious but tamable, Nivastok Shieldbearers are one of the best \rcompanions for Venomancers.",
41989: "Both Archosaur and Thousand Streams are encircled by \rthe Wraiths. A huge number of Malicious Cadevils are marching \rtowards East Barrier Village and South Barrier Village.\rThe two villages are covered by the air of death.",
41990: "Headless Knights work for the Wraiths and wreak havoc wherever they go.\rPlease kill them whenever you see them.",
41991: "Remember, you should overcome the fear in your heart \rin battle with those headless wraiths!",
41992: "Snow Hounds are the best friends for people living in cold areas.\rBut now they are going to be wiped out by the Lethal \rAraneid Sharpfangs.",
41993: "Mysterious amulets you got from Nivastok Braves.\rPlace them in a snowfield, and they will automatically \rform into an avatar-like image.",
41994: "Gnosis Treerats used to live harmoniously with humans,\rbut the Wraiths corrupted them and turned them into cruel creatures.",
41995: "Conquesting Dustwraiths live in Sundown Town.\rThey use their cookware as weapons to fight.",
42336: "<span style='color:#ff0f85'>War Avatar only for rookies. Not included in War Avatar Book.</span>",
42337: "<span style='color:#ff0f85'>War Avatar only for rookies. Not included in War Avatar Book.</span>",
42338: "<span style='color:#ff0f85'>War Avatar only for rookies. Not included in War Avatar Book.</span>",
46910: "Here is the place where the dream began and the place\rwhere reality showed its power. Some people started\rtheir heroic dream here, while others surrendered it\rfor a life of peace. However, Etherblade's long history\rproves to the world that those who persevered are worthy\rof respect, and those who returned are to be cherished.",
46911: "The wild Barbarians, the mysterious Venomancers, and the archaic\rbuildings and bestial statues of the Untamed make up the savage\rCity of the Lost. Though these heroes have fought and died in\rbloody battles, none have regretted it. Their true desire, though,\rwas peace, and now that they have achieved it in their home they\rseek to protect the stability and prosperity of the world.",
46912: "The City of Raging Tides lies to the southeast of Perfect World, on Barrier Island\rin the Sea of Reality. Long ago, when the Wraiths first invaded Perfect World, the\rTideborn elders cast a spell called the Dimensional Cataclysm to defeat them, but in\rdoing so their land was cut off from Perfect World for many years. Though they have\rsince returned, so too have their immortal enemies: the vicious Nightspikes.",
46913: "Tellus City is the home of the Earthguard, warriors chosen by\rRadiance to protect Perfect World from the Wraiths. Though long\rburied beneath the surface, when the Wraiths once again threatened\rPerfect World, they emerged from their long slumber to do battle once more.",
46914: "The Reapers were once the children of the Divine Child, but when their\rcreator was struck down they were given mortal lives so as to outlive him.\rTheir descendants, the Nightshades, came to Perfect World aboard a flying ship\rand settled on an uncharted island in the northeast. Expanding their ship into\rthe city of Dawnglory, they have protected Perfect World from within the shadows,\ronly recently stepping into the light to openly battle the Wraiths and Nightmares.",
46915: "The Winged Elves are noble and dignified, flying high above Perfect World\ron brilliant feathered wings. Their people are skill Archers and powerful\rClerics, their homes elegant and atmospheric, and their land full of\rforests of idyllic beauty. Beneath the canopy of the great tree lies\rthe beautiful heart of their territory: the City of the Plume."};



