, 100: "Applejack lives and works at Sweet Apple Acres \rwith her grandmother Granny Smith; her big brother \rBig McIntosh; her little sister Apple Bloom;\r and her dog Winona. She represents the element\r of honesty. Applejack is dependable and loyal, \ralways willing to help anybody in need.",
101: "Rainbow Dash is responsible for maintaining the weather\r and clearing the skies in Ponyville. As a huge fan of \rThe Wonderbolts, she dreams of one day joining their elite \rflying group.  She represents the element of loyalty.",
102: "Fluttershy lives in a small cottage near the Everfree Forest\r and is an animal caretaker, the most prominent of her charges\r being Angel the bunny. She represents the element of kindness.",
103: "Twilight Sparkle moved from Canterlot to Ponyville to \rstudy the magic of friendship, and regularly sent friendship\r reports to Princess Celestia. She lives in Golden Oak Library\r with Spike, her assistant. Twilight Sparkle represents the\r element of magic.",
104: "Pinkie Pie is energetic and sociable, and she represents\r the element of laughter. She works at Sugarcube Corner and \rlives on the bakery's second floor with Gummy, her pet toothless\r baby alligator. She writes and performs many songs, and\r is known for many comical gags.",
105: "Rarity works as both a fashion designer and as a\r seamstress at her own shop in Ponyville, the Carousel\r Boutique. She has a sister named Sweetie Belle and a white\r Persian cat named Opalescence. She represents the element\r of generosity. "/**/
